        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 5:25PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Decatur, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntsville, Decatur, Madison, Athens, Hartselle, Redstone Arsenal,
Priceville, Trinity, Owens Cross Roads, and Courtland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
